06699nam a22010455i 9783110892512DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20122003gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831108925127 a10.1515/97831108925122doi  a(DE-B1597)56149  a(OCoLC)979748685  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aBS1560b.T44 2003 7aREL0060902bisacsh04a224.906222  aBC 75252rvk0(DE-625)rvk/9682:00aThematic Threads in the Book of the Twelve /ced. by Aaron Schart, Paul L. Redditt.  aReprint 2012 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2012] 4c©2003  a1 online resource (376 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aBeihefte zur Zeitschrift für die alttestamentliche Wissenschaft ,x0934-2575 ;v3250 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aFor some years the view has become established that the Book of the Twelve is a systematically structured literary unity. An exegesis which takes the final canonical text seriously undertakes to understand the structure and theological intention of this unity. The papers collected here attempt to reveal significant structures which overarch the individual components. Particular emphasis is placed on the reconstruction of thematic threads which are created when individual prophets take up topics from their predecessors (e.g. Jehovah's Day, conversion, role of the peoples) and intensify them. The papers were written between 1999 and 2002 under the aegis of the Society of Biblical Literature's Working Group on The Formation of the Book of the Twelve.  aSeit einigen Jahren hat sich die Auffassung durchgesetzt, dass das Zwölfprophetenbuch eine planvoll gestaltete literarische Großeinheit ist. Eine den kanonischen Endtext ernst nehmende Exegese macht sich zur Aufgabe, diese Einheit in Aufbau und theologischem Anliegen zu verstehen. Die versammelten Beiträge gehen signifikanten, die Einzelschriften übergreifenden Strukturen nach. Besonderes Gewicht wird auf die Rekonstruktion thematischer Fäden gelegt, die dadurch entstehen, dass die einzelnen Propheten Themen ihrer Vorgänger (z.B. Tag Jahwes, Umkehr, Rolle der Völker) aufgreifen und neu zuspitzen. Die Beiträge entstanden 1999-2002 im Rahmen der Arbeitsgruppe The Formation of the Book of the Twelve der Society of Biblical Literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aBibelkanon. 4aExegese. 4aKleine Propheten. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh1 aAlbertz, Rainer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaumann, Gerlinde, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraaten, Laurie J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConrad, Edgar W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrenshaw, James L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEgo, Beate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEverson, A. Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerstenberger, Erhard S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHouse, Paul R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNogalski, James D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRedditt, Paul L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRedditt, Paul L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRedditt, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchart, Aaron, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchart, Aaron, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchultz, Richard L., econtributor.